The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Fashion contention

 One of Indias best-known fashion writers in the global arena, Hindol Sengupta has recently completed Indian Fashion, his maiden book on the Indian fashion industry. The first-ever comprehensive documentation of our country?s vibrant fashion scene, the book is an ultimate guide to the styles of what is perhaps the world?s most dynamic fashion market, as well as of the people who create them. Presented by Oxford Bookstore and Pearson Education, the Calcutta launch of the book is followed by a panel discussion on Global Trends in Indian Fashion. With renowned fashion designers like Sabyasachi Mukherjee, Kiran Uttam Ghosh, Anamika Khanna and Monapali as panelists, the discussion is augmented and enriched by audio-visual presentations from the designers? latest collections. A must-witness event for those interested in fashion and style, or simply in dressing well. Moderator: Hindol Sengupta.

 Event: Book launch followed by a panel discussion on Indian fashion trends

 When: Today at 6.30 pm

 Where: Oxford Bookstore, 17 Park Street




